cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the problem of detecting automated social agents on social media platforms. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes a machine learning approach to detect bots. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the societal impact of bots on social media. It could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the detection of bots is a security concern on social media platforms. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a system to detect bots based on network topology.
